1
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,000
Hi... Danny?
你好... Danny?

2
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:15,000
Hi Nancy. Hi. How are you?
你好, Nancy. 你好. 你好吗?

3
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:21,300
Fine, thanks. Nice tuxedo.
很好, 谢谢. 礼服不错.

4
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:26,000
I'm... I'm... I'm going to a wedding.
我, 我, 我要去参加一个婚礼.

5
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:32,300
For a minute there, you looked like one of those balloon-delivery guys.
有那么一分钟, 你看上去像个送气球的.

6
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:36,100
The balloons are for the wedding.
这气球是为婚礼准备的.

7
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:37,502
Oh.
Oh.

8
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:43,500
The couple is Danish, and the Danes have an old custom.
这对新婚夫妇是丹麦人, 丹麦人有一个古老的风俗.

9
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:47,200
Actually, it's not that old, but the balloons are part of it.
事实上, 并没有那么古老, 但气球是其中的一部分.

10
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:49,300
Part of the wedding.
是婚礼的一部分.

11
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:50,000
Yes.
是的.

12
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:52,464
Everybody has something.
每个国家的人都有自己的传统.

13
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:54,150
Americans throw birdseed. 
美国人扔鸟食.

14
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:56,405
The Japanese have rubber cakes.
日本人有橡皮蛋糕.

15
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:59,900
In Liechtenstein, they kidnap the bride from the reception.
在Liechtenstein, 人们把新娘从喜宴上抢走.

16
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,400
... Or is that the Zimbabweans?
...或者那是Zimbabwean人的习俗吧?

17
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:07,800
You know, Nancy, I was just on my way out.
You know, Nancy, 我正要外出.

18
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,150
Of course. Don't let me keep you.
当然. 别因为我而耽搁了.

19
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:13,400
You don't want to be late for a wedding, especially if you're in the bridal party.
你当然不想参加婚礼迟到, 尤其如果你是新娘家的客人的话.

20
00:01:13,450 --> 00:01:14,700
Are you the best man?
你是伴郎吗?

21
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:19,950
No. Yes. Sort of. Nice talking to you. Bye.
不是. 是的. 算是吧. 很高兴和你聊天. 再见.

